      "id": "P_MODEL_A_DYNAMIC_SUPPLY_ELECTRICAL_LEVEL",
      "observable_contract": "Model a dynamic-supply electrical level driver. Compute the input level relative to the local rails, not global ground. When `V(vdd, vss)` is at least `vsup_min`, drive `out` to the local low or high rail-derived level according to whether the normalized input exceeds `vth_frac`. When the supply is below `vsup_min`, drive `out` to the local low level. Smooth the output with `transition()`.",
